Hot take: AI doesn't replace designers. It shifts the bottleneck.

**Old world:** Generation is expensive. You hire artists, writers, level designers. Each asset costs real human hours. Curation happens naturally because you can't afford to make everything.

**New world:** Generation is cheap. You can produce 100 variations of anything in minutes. But now the bottleneck is *selection* — which 5 of those 100 actually belong in your game?

**The thesis:** Authorship becomes selection, not fabricat
